1781978674193810	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEznAE		item.create	bn-1np	{"description":"**What:** Implement backward demand/ROI analysis (plan.md В§10.1 phase 7, В§11.3): starting from exports +\nassertions + requested debug resources, propagate required regions backward through each op via\n`OpContract::required_inputs(requested_output_region, params)`. Provide correct ROI functions for the op families\nthat exist (pointwise = same region; convolution/blur = expand by halo; crop/pad/resize/warp = inverse footprint +\nreconstruction halo; composite = target + source-where-mask-nonzero; SDF/EDT = whole connected domain / full image;\nhistogram/statistics = whole demanded input). Strengthen dead-node elimination using the demand set.\n**Acceptance:** for each op family, `required_inputs` returns a region that provably contains all contributing source pixels (tested by comparing ROI-restricted vs full execution вҖ” must be pixel-identical inside the demanded region); a node outside the demand set is eliminated; ROI of a pointwise chain equals the export region.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` ROI suite вҖ” per-op-family \"ROI execution == full execution inside demanded region\" differential (exact for exact ops) + dead-node-elimination test; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§10.1 (phase 7), В§11.3; IR_SPEC В§18; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§12.2.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor [M0 bn-kfw]; M1 exit (full op set to exercise) [bn-2rx].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"l","title":"Backward ROI + halo propagation through the demand graph"}	blake3:Wk8f0KAeA-gI65vP5vzDrZY-dLE2YQfdbdJZM5G4x9U
1781978674305153	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEznQE		item.create	bn-6kl	{"description":"**What:** Define the logical tile model (configurable base tile, initially 128Г—128 / 256Г—256; per-op input halo\nper output tile) and a `MaskTileSummary` structure over mask tiles (min/max coverage, nonzero count, bounds of\nnonzero) per plan.md В§11.2/В§11.4. Empty masked tiles become identity without evaluating the expensive branch;\nfull masked tiles may skip blend-mask reads.\n**Acceptance:** tile occupancy classification (empty/full/mixed) is correct on rect/ellipse/scattered masks; the summary's nonzero-bounds match `mask.bounds`; an empty-tile fast path is provably identity (differential vs dense).\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` tile-summary suite (occupancy correctness, bounds agreement, empty-tile identity); `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§11.2, В§11.4.\n**Depends on:** Backward ROI + halo propagation.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"m","title":"Tile model + sparse mask tile summaries (occupancy: empty/full/mixed)"}	blake3:5csf7LIQB9O21PFr_4FJPsBOSRFEEh9K6x9koFcsioE
1781978674421978	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzngE		item.create	bn-3mm	{"description":"**What:** A demand-driven tile/strip executor for pointwise ops (plan.md В§10.2, В§11): evaluate only demanded tiles,\nreuse tile buffers under liveness, honor halos, and keep a bounded working set. Immutable logical resources;\nphysical buffer reuse invisible to semantics.\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION В§3.x tiled==whole property):** tiled execution of a pointwise chain is **bit-identical** to whole-image execution for exact ops and within tolerance for bounded ops; no tile-seam artifacts; working-set memory is bounded (measured) regardless of image size.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” \"tiled == whole-image\" differential for the pointwise MVP/M1 chain + a bounded-memory assertion (peak resident under a cap for a 4K input); `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§10.2, В§11.1; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§2.4, В§12.2.\n**Depends on:** Tile model + sparse mask tile summaries.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"l","title":"Tile executor for pointwise operations"}	blake3:hh-52ey2EhnzQLXa2NeLOvhOnlSJiSkV0vkQFHYwixs
1781978674536481	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEznwE		item.create	bn-3r8	{"description":"**What:** Extend the tile executor to neighborhood ops (convolution / gaussian_blur) with correct per-tile input\nhalos, and prove equivalence to the whole-image reference (plan.md В§20 PR 21).\n**Acceptance (AGENT_VERIFICATION В§3.3):** tiled convolution == whole-image `filter.convolve` reference (exact for integer fixtures, within declared tolerance for f32); no visible tile grid (the В§13 bug-taxonomy \"tile grid visible\" must not occur); correct results across all boundary modes at tile edges.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” tiled-vs-whole differential for `filter.convolve` + `filter.gaussian_blur` across boundary modes, with an error map saved on failure; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§20 (PR 21), В§11.3; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§3.3, В§13.\n**Depends on:** Tile executor for pointwise operations; filter.convolve [M1 bn-21l].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"m","title":"Tiled convolution + whole-image differential equivalence"}	blake3:WiF82B2OAjMzWyBZ1Z4ozqmjAGkeXOUqhJQsxLe7GD4
1781978674647341	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzoAE		item.create	bn-25j	{"description":"**What:** Make tiled reductions (`analyze.statistics`, `analyze.histogram`, and assertion reductions)\n**deterministic** via fixed merge trees independent of tile scheduling/thread count (plan.md В§11.2 \"deterministic\nmerge trees on the reference backend\"; bug taxonomy \"iterative/reduction order\" in В§13).\n**Acceptance:** reduction result is bit-identical across thread counts {1,2,8} and across tile sizes; matches the sequential whole-image reduction; floating accumulation order is fixed and documented.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” reduction determinism across thread/tile configs (bit-identical) + agreement with the M1 whole-image statistics; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§11.2; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§13 (nondeterministic reduction signature).\n**Depends on:** analyze.statistics + analyze.histogram [M1 bn-2fp]; Tile executor for pointwise operations.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"m","title":"Deterministic reductions (stable merge trees)"}	blake3:yfnbXoYYZSdmQpM6IiZdARS_mGVbOgPwR5ADeNVegNM
1781978674759397	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzoQE		item.create	bn-1rk	{"description":"**What:** A content-addressed result cache keyed per plan.md В§10.3:\n`hash(op_id + op_semantic_version + canonical_params + ordered_input_content_hashes + resource_semantics + seed +\nbackend_semantics_version)` using BLAKE3. Cache entries carry validation metadata and must NOT be reused across\nincompatible semantic versions. Hash content + relevant metadata, never a path.\n**Acceptance:** identical subgraph вҶ’ cache hit returns output **equal to uncached** (AGENT_VERIFICATION В§2.4); changing op semantic version / a semantic param / an input's content вҶ’ cache miss; cache replay of a fully-cached plan executes **zero** pure producer nodes (trace-verified); a stale/incompatible entry is rejected, not silently reused (bug taxonomy \"cache-only failure\").\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” cache hit==uncached, key-sensitivity matrix, and a \"replay executes zero producers\" trace assertion; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§10.3; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§2.4, В§13; M0_DECISIONS.md D4 (BLAKE3).\n**Depends on:** Canonicalization + BLAKE3 hashing [M0 bn-1e0]; Graph resolver + executor [M0 bn-kfw].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"l","title":"Content-addressed cache (BLAKE3 keys, semantic-version-aware, replay)"}	blake3:vR1ZB-YMvmw5Q1LNHOKtJZ_X2SVondkomFGaLkag05U
1781978674878918	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzogE		item.create	bn-28m	{"description":"**What:** The safe, handwritten canonical simplifications from plan.md В§10.1 phase 8 (NOT e-graph, NOT GPU pointwise\nfusion вҖ” those are M8/M3): constant folding, identity-node elimination, common-subexpression elimination, and\nconversion cancellation (e.g. `premultiplyвҲҳunpremultiply` where Оұ>Оө; `convert(AвҶ’B)вҲҳconvert(BвҶ’A)` вҶ’ identity), with\nbarriers that forbid rewriting across requested debug materialization, assertions observing an intermediate,\nstochastic nodes, and nonlinear encodings unless algebra proves safety (ALIEN_OPS В§13.2/В§13.3).\n**Acceptance:** each rewrite preserves the semantic hash of OUTPUTS (differential: simplified vs unsimplified outputs identical for exact ops); CSE collapses duplicate subgraphs (node-count drops, output unchanged); barriers prevent rewriting across a `debug.materialize` / assertion; simplification is disable-able.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” output-equivalence differential (simplified == unsimplified) + per-rewrite side-condition tests + barrier tests + a disable flag; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§10.1 (phase 8); ALIEN_OPS В§13.2, В§13.3.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor [M0 bn-kfw].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"m","title":"Graph simplification: constant folding, identity elimination, CSE, conversion cancellation"}	blake3:LcdWiTMSsr6HVfeM7qMI0ViZzB6464YsnNb7a0pncCs
1781978674990928	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzowE		item.create	bn-1hv	{"description":"**What:** `paintop graph plan.json --out graph.{dot,svg}` and the `graph.dot` evidence artifact (plan.md В§15.4,\nВ§15.1): render the normalized DAG with op ids, ports, resource types, and demand/ROI annotations.\n**Acceptance:** emitted DOT is valid and round-trips through Graphviz; node/edge set matches the normalized graph exactly; ports + resource kinds are labeled; the evidence bundle's `graph.dot` matches the executed graph.\n**Exit gate:** `cargo test` вҖ” DOT structural test (nodes/edges match normalized plan) + valid-DOT parse; `paintop graph` integration test; `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§15.4, В§15.1.\n**Depends on:** Graph resolver + executor [M0 bn-kfw]; paintop CLI [M0 bn-ajx].\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"s","title":"Graph visualization: paintop graph вҶ’ dot/svg"}	blake3:93ARC6F19hciu4pc_Dzt1_7bacnYWQGf0sQyDyw0_ik
1781978675104957	paintop-dev	itc:v3:AWKTkkmcyckyeZEAAAAAQa6q3a6te0AAAAEzpAE		item.create	bn-1r2	{"description":"**What:** Close M2 (plan.md В§19 M2 exit criteria) by wiring the milestone's guarantees into a CI gate: (1)\nwhole-image and tiled outputs identical for exact operations; (2) ROI execution differentially equivalent to full\nexecution; (3) a small masked edit on a 4K image touches **only** the predicted (halo-expanded) tile set вҖ”\nmeasured via the trace's requested/executed/identity tile counts; (4) cache replay shows zero unnecessary\nexecution.\n**Acceptance:** all four criteria pass in CI on representative plans; the 4K masked-edit test asserts executed-tile count вүӨ the conservative halo-expanded prediction (AGENT_VERIFICATION В§12.2); performance/tile-count artifacts are uploaded.\n**Exit gate:** CI \"M2 compiler\" job green (the four differential/efficiency criteria + artifact upload); `just check` вҶ’ 0.\n**Refs:** plan.md В§19 (M2 exit criteria), В§11; AGENT_VERIFICATION В§12.\n**Depends on:** ALL M2 bones.\n","kind":"task","labels":["group-m2"],"parent":"bn-97e","size":"m","title":"M2 exit gate: tiled==whole, ROI==full, 4K touch-only-predicted-tiles, cache zero-recompute"}	blake3:6JIFLs2w0K8u63SlpfJBtf374w8B3rdOI0p8_7Kfa28
